
[1]thundering

   THUN'DERING, ppr. Making the noise of an electrical explosion; uttering
   a loud sound; fulminating denunciations.

   THUN'DERING, n. The report of an electrical explosion; thunder.

   Entreat the Lord that there by no more mighty thunderings and hail.
   Ex.9.
